T1	Intervention 484 690	randomized to an intravenous group (n = 250), receiving 50 U/kg of unfractionated heparin (maximal dose 5,000 U) intravenously, and an intra-arterial group (n = 250) receiving the same dose intra-arterially
T2	Intervention 692 836	All patients received a vasodilator "cocktail" intra-arterially and underwent cardiac catheterization using a 5F introducer sheath and catheters
T3	Intervention 838 1026	The activated clotting time was measured at the end of the procedure. All patients received hemostasis with a radial compression device (TR Band), applied after sheath removal, for 2 hours
T4	Intervention 1028 1123	A plethysmographic evaluation for RAO was performed at 24 hours and 30 days after the procedure
